# Queues and cron

## BullMQ queues (app/server/queues)

- backupQueue.ts — backups
- plaidSyncQueue.ts — Plaid transaction sync
- plaidSyncBalanceQueue.ts — Plaid balance-only sync
- recalculateQueue.ts — forecasting recalculations

Use app/server/clients/queuesClient.ts to obtain connections. For long-running or high-latency operations, prefer enqueuing a job and returning early from API handlers.

## Scheduled jobs (nuxt-cron, app/server/cron)

- backup.daily.ts — periodic backup
- plaid.daily.ts — Plaid sync heartbeat
- plaid-balance.hourly.ts — Plaid balance refresh
- recalculate.hourly.ts — trigger forecast recalculations
- bill-reminders.hourly.ts — evaluate bill reminders
- crypto-balance.hourly.ts — EVM wallet/token balance sync

Cron tasks call underlying services (e.g., PlaidSyncService, AlchemyService) and may enqueue additional work.

## Admin/task endpoints (ad-hoc triggers)

- app/server/api/tasks/*:
  - backup.ts, migrate.ts
  - recalculate.ts
  - sync-plaid.ts, sync-plaid-balance.ts
  - check-* (health checks / consistency)
  - sync-google-sheet*.post.ts (aux data import)
  - various test-* endpoints for controlled scenarios

Guard these behind admin or internal tokens where appropriate; see server/lib/requireAdmin.ts and env-driven guards in some handlers.
